review_text: First Crack is one of my favorite coffee shops. However, its regrettable to note the poor service and hospitality at First Crack on Bumi Street during my recent visit. I came with my wife, parents, and my 1.5-year-old child. Right from the start, I requested a baby chair for my child. I waited for 10 minutes, but the chair never came. I asked the manager twice, but there was no friendliness, just a curt response that theyll find one. I waited again, but no one came to us. So, I asked the manager for the third time, and all he said was that they only have 2 baby chairs, and they were all in use. I lost my patience, and the manager disappeared and never came back to me. I had to go to the 2nd floor by myself to check if the baby chair was still in use. Apparently, it wasnt being used; no one had sat in the baby chair. I came back down to the 1st floor and asked the staff to bring it to me. Again, without politeness and hospitality, and with a defensive attitude, he made an excuse that he didnt serve that particular area, so he wasnt aware of the baby chair. Such a very stupid reason. I finally got the baby chair after waiting for 45 minutes, and my family had to take turns eating to take care of my son. A premium coffee shop with the WORST service and hospitality by far. Its disappointing that a coffee shop of this size didnt consider the ratio or minimum number of baby chairs needed.

review_text: Bakerzin offers a delightful retreat for those seeking a moment of indulgence amidst the hustle and bustle of Jakarta. Nestled in the upscale mall, this outpost of renowned dessert haven delivers on its promise of exquisite treats and culinary delights. As one would expect from Bakerzin, the dessert are undisputed stars of the show. From rich and delicate pastries bustling flavor, each creation is testament to the artistry and skill of pastry chefs. Bakerzin Signature s Chocolate Cake, Chocolate Souffle and Creme Brulee,Bakerzin s menu offers something to satisfy every sweet tooth. The ambience at Bakerzin strikes a balance between sophistication and comfort. Chic decor, plush seating create an inviting atmosphere perfect for enjoying a leisurely dessert date or catching up with friends over coffee. However, during peak hours, the space can get a bit crowded, so its advisable to plan your visit accordingly. Service at Bakerzin is attentive and courteous, with staff members readily available  to assist with menu recommendation or special requests. Despite the bustling environment, they strive to ensure that every guest feels welcomed and well cared for enhancing the overall dining experience.

They should not put up a menu that they can NOT cook. My potato came raw on the inside, and I asked them to cook it again, only to find its still raw. Im SO disappointed as I used to come here every weekend for years, and now that Im in town, I wanted some nostalgic tastes, and its heartbreaking. Out of 6 food that we ordered, only the chicken drum steak came out good. What a sad sad thing. I had so much hope for such a big establishment.
The chocochip & double choco crokies are too sweet for me. The sweetness is very dominant so i cannot taste the overall croisant + cookies well.

As for the pastries ordered, everything was okay and delicious. The lotus is really sweet, its better to just share it, not one person at a time. The potatoes are also delicious. The button on the table to call the waitress doesnt seem to work, because you press it all the time until you finally have to call it directly.

Came here because there was an International Womans Day 2023 event from the office. Orders are handled by the committee coordinator. The atmosphere of the restaurant is surrounded by glass and there are tables and seating outdoors. Inside there is a restaurant for bakery, ice cream and Indonesian food. To order food, I ordered Nasi Goreng Sei and Scarlett Eldeberry. Because we ordered food in a large group, around 40-50 orders, so there were some foods that arrived late and double orders. It seems like it might never handle consecutive orders because the basic restaurant itself is suitable for coffee, tea and those who want WFC. But in the end the order was handled quite well. In terms of food, their mainstay is drinks, especially tea and coffee. For the food I chose, I chose recommendations from the menu. If you want to eat heavily, I recommend eating Indonesian food, because my colleague said that Indonesian food is delicious, compared to western food. Their desserts and appetizers are also delicious, because its a basic restaurant for hanging out. They also provide tea packages which can be purchased here and ice cream packages. Vegetarian options: There are salads.
review_translated_text: Kesini datang karena ada acara International Woman Day 2023 dari kantor. Pemesanan dihandle sama koordinator panitia. Untuk suasana restoran nya dikelilingi kaca dan terdapat meja dan tempat duduk di outdoor. Didalamnya sendiri ada restoran untuk bakery, eskrim dan Indonesian food. Untuk pemesanan makan saya pesen Nasi Goreng Sei dan Scarlett Eldeberry. Karena kami pesan makanan dalam grup besar, sekitar 40-50 pesanan, jadi ada beberapa makanan yg telat datang dan double pesanan. Sepertinya memang mungkin tidak pernah handle pemesanan beruntun karena basic restoran nya sendiri cocok buat ngopi, teh dan yang mau wfc. Tapi akhirnya pesanan terhandle cukup baik. Untuk review segi makanan, memang andalan mereka adalah minuman khususnya teh dan kopi. Untuk makanan yg saya pilih memang saya pilih rekomendasi dari menunya, kalau anda mau makan berat saya sarankan makan Indonesian Food nya, karena rekan saya bilang untuk Indonesian food ya enak, dibanding western. Untuk dessert dan appetizer mereka juga enak, karena basic restoran untuk nongkrong. Mereka juga menyediakan paket teh yg di bisa di beli disini dan paket es krim. Vegetarian options: Salad ada.

review_text: This place is really cool, only the tables are small. The location is a bit in an alley and there is a bit of hiding   bonus view of Ciliwung coooooyy. Varied menu, okay prices for a coffee shop in Jakarta. Try the butter beer, its really thick, its delicious . Well, if you come here, try the Quesadilla, its really delicious, its real, its not fake

Garlic honey chicken rice is the perfect combination of garlic and honey chicken flavors, a little too sweet but covered by the taste of the garlic and the savory and juicy chicken. The Hazelnut Chocolate is also delicious and sweet but just right on the tongue for its taste. And finally, the savory and crunchy cheese sambosa is of course delicious combined with chili sauce. Value 8/10 Recommended
review_translated_text: Nasi ayam garlic honey perpafuan rasa ayam bawang putih dan madu yang pas, sedikit terlalu manis tapi tertutupi rasa dari garlicnya dan ayamnya yang gurih an juicy. Hazelnut Chocolatenya juga enak dan manis tapi pas dilidah untuk rasanya. Dan terakhir sambosa kejunya yang gurih dan garing tentunya enak dipadukan dengan saus sambal. Nilai 8/10 Recommended

review_text: Entering this cafe area, I think you will get lost, because the place is inside a residential area. It turned out to be a really fun place. When you go deeper, you can already feel the natural atmosphere in this cafe. The eyes are presented with a beautiful and beautiful view. This cafe provides menus using barcodes on every table, we can even pay on the website using Go Pay, or other available payments. In terms of price, its very affordable. Drinks range from 15K - 30K, snacks & main courses range from 18K - 50K
review_translated_text: Masuk ke area cafe ini kirain nyasar, karena tempatnya masuk didalam pemukiman rumah warga. Ternyata tempatnya asyik banget. pas masuk lebih kedalam,udah bisa ngerasain atmosphere alam di cafe ini. Mata udah disuguhkan dengan pemandangan indah nan cantik. cafe ini menyediakan menu pake barcode di setiap meja,,bahkan kita bisa sekalian payment di websitenya pake Go pay, atau pembayaran lainnya yang tersedia. Dari segi harga affordable banget. minumannya rangenya dari 15K - 30K snack & maincoursenya dari range 18K- 50K

review_text: nice place, the food is also delicious!!, but if you come here late at night just bring autan just to be safe

review_text: The food is delicious, the service has adapted to the digital era, scan the order then pay, the atmosphere is by the river so it feels different even though the location is in Jakarta, the prices are quite commensurate with the taste of the food & drinks provided.
review_translated_text: Makanannya enak, pelayanannya sudah beradaptasi dengan era digital, scan pesan lalu bayar, suasananya pinggir sungai jadinya terasa beda padahal lokasinya di Jakarta, harga lumayan sepandan dengan cita rasa makanan & minuman yang disediakan.

review_text: The place is in a small alley, fits 1 car. Around 100 meters turn right, the parking lot is quite large. From the parking lot, walk a little to the right, go down. Not afternoon. The place is nice, green with lots of trees. View of Ciliwung Lake. To order food, scan the barcode on the table or order directly at the cashier. The food menu is quite varied, I ordered dori sambal matah, the price is 50 Rban. Pretty good. Cappuccino coffee 37 thousand, delicious. Mineral water 12 thousand. I like the taste of the coffee, its not bitter. Overall it was fun eating here. Cool place, delicious food and drinks. The price is a bit expensive in my opinion but still affordable.
review_translated_text: Tempatnya masuk gang kecil,muat 1 mobil. Sekitar 100 mtr belok ke kanan,parkiran lumayan luas. Dari parkiran masih jalan sedikit ke kanan,turun ke bawah. Bukanya siang. Tempatnya bagus,hijau banyak pohon. Pemandangan danau ciliwung. Untuk pesan makanan scan barcode yang dimeja atau bisa langsung pesan  di kasir. Menu makanan cukup bervariasi,saya pesan dori sambal matah,harga 50 rban. Lumayan enak. Kopi cappucino 37 rb,enak. Air mineral 12 rb.  Suka dengan taste kopinya,tidak pahit. Overall asyik makan di sini. Tempat kece,makanan dan minuman enak. Harga agak sedikit mahal menurut saya tapi masih affordable.

review_text: The food is all delicious
review_translated_text: Makanannya enak semua

review_text: Cool place and great food taste
Just an ordinary place. Not too wide for visitors to sit. At dusk its a bit scary because its on the edge of the Ciliwung River. Sorry for the comment.

I went to the east corner in Condet, the place is secluded, I almost didnt think there was a cafe there because it was in the same area as the residents houses. Came here on weekdays, in the evening after the rain, the atmosphere was really beautiful. Very suitable for people who like to go to cafes alone to enjoy the natural atmosphere. Ordering has also been made easier because you just scan the barcode, choose the menu you like and then pay. You can use applications like OVO, GoPay and you can also deposit cash at the cashier. The matcha is really delicious, soft and creamy
review_translated_text: Aku pergi ke sudut timur yg ada di condet, tempatnya terpencil, hampir gak nyangka disitu ada kafe karena masih satu kawasan sm rumah warga gitu. Kesini weekdays, malem setelah hujan, syahdu banget suasananya. Cocok banget buat orang yg suka ke cafe sendiri menikmati suasana alam. Untuk order juga udah dipermudah karena tinggal scan barcode, pilih menu yg km suka trus bayar deh. Bisa lewat aplikasi kaya ovo, gopay dan bisa batar cash juga di kasir. Matcha nya enak banget, lembut dan creamyyy

review_text: 7 cellphones cant scan barcodes. there is a service tax, but it is dirty and many tables are filled with dirty plates used by other people. There are lots of employees but none of them can lift dirty dishes. Bones left by people eating are not removed, left on the table.
The place is more cool because there are lots of trees. Plus the food is really delicious. The price is also affordable...
review_translated_text: Lebih ke adem ya tempat nya karna banyak pohon . Ditambah makanan ya enak2 banget. Untuk harga juga affordable..

review_text: Not Recommended! Overall bad service with poor service, the waiting time for food can be up to 40 minutes, for bad food at such an expensive price its not worth the price. review_text: Heng Heng Laksa n Nasi lemak authentic Singapore.. recommended

Apparently they have a lot of food choices to enjoy and coffee drinks to sip along the meeting. The place is comfortable, spacious and clean. First timer to be here and immediately recommended to try Heng Heng Katong Laksa. It is marvelously delicious! Probably the most authentic laksa Ive ever tasted so far. Apart from laksa, there are also other special menus that are ready to be tried and will not disappoint  . Then try the Pizza Plate which is bigger than the palm of your hand. Its also delicious and really satisfying if you look for meeting places while eating and drinking. For coffee, here is the Javanese Coffee Shop  . Theres no need to doubt the pleasure. Dont think about whether the coffee is affiliated with Isril or not because this is local coffee, not like the shop next door  . Alright, okay. So what else? Theres gelato here, Korean chicken, then theres soto too, and theres a barber shop upstairs too. Its just a shame that Gelato only operates from midday to afternoon. So if you want to come here and enjoy all the food and drinks here, you can try it between midday and evening. But since morning, its been there but the service is limited. Thats all. For visitors, please maintain cleanliness and mind your tone of voice. Dont be too noisy, respect the presence of other visitors, and keep this communal space a social place with appropriate etiquette in public places. Not a place for children and in terms of security it is also not kids friendly or family friendly. This place is more suitable for colleague meetings and WFA work.
review_translated_text: Apparently they have a lot of food choices to enjoy and coffee drinks to sip along the meeting. Tempatnya nyaman, luas, dan bersih. First timer to be here dan langsung disaranin untuk nyoba Heng Heng Katong Laksa. It is marvelously delicious! Probably the most authentic laksa I ever tasted so far. Selain laksa, ada juga menu2 khas lainnya yang siap untuk dicoba dan tidak akan mengecewakan  . Terus sempet nyoba juga Pizza Plate-nya yang seukuran lebi besar dari telapak tangan. Enak juga dan puas banget intinya kalo nyari2 tempat meeting sambi makan dan minum. Untuk kopinya, di sini ada Toko Kopi Djawa  . Uda ngga usah diragukan yah kenikmatannya. Ngga usah mikir kopinya ada afiliasi sama Isril ato kaga karena ini kopi lokal, ngga kaya toko sebelah  . Alright, oke. Trus apalagi yah. Di sini ada Gelato, ayam Korea, trus ada soto juga, dan ada tukang cukur juga di lantai atas. Cuma sayangnya si Gelato keknya baru beroperasi tu di jam siang ke sore. Jadi kalo mo ke sini dan nikmatin semua makanan dan minuman yg ada di sini, bisa dicoba antara waktu siang ke sore yah. Tapi kalo dari pagi, uda ada tapi terbatas aja pelayanannya. Uda gitu aja. Untuk para pengunjung, tolong tetep jaga kebersihan dan mind your tone of voice yah. Jangan terlalu berisik, hormati kehadiran pengunjung lain, dan tetap jaga communal space ini sebagai tempat sosial dengan tata krama yang sepantasnya di tempat publik. Bukan tempat untuk anak2 dan secara keamanan juga ngga kids friendly dan family friendly. Tempat ini lebi cocok untuk meeting kolega dan kerja WFA.

review_text: This is my first time in Roemah Polonia. It s indeed worth to try and not for only once. The staffs are really friendly and give fast & delightful service to the guests. The food are truly affordablec yet they are surprisingly scrumptious. The ambience is peaceful and beautifully decorated. Would love to be here for other occasion!!

One of the hidden gems (which is actually not very hidden for eastern children) When I came here it was a bit quiet so it was good to chat. I deliberately chose to sit in the outdoor area because it was evening and the air wasnt hot because it was raining that day. Overall, the ambience is good. Lots of plants, wide lawns, and the sound of water splashing from bamboo into water barrels. The bonus is that there are a few mosquitoes, but dont worry, you can chase them away using a fan. Suggestion: Come in the afternoon or evening so its not hot and its more aesthetic because the lights are already on. Order Beef Teriyaki, surprisingly delicious. The meat is not too sweet and you can request the eggs half boiled   The Dory Salted Egg is also tasty and has chili sauce. Thai Tea is a bit sweet but thats my taste. Unfortunately, I havent had the chance to try the coffee yet. Ill try it when I go there again.

review_text: One of the hidden gems in East Jakarta. The location is in a complex like that. We were confused, because there was no big sign indicating it. From the outside, just look for one with a large parking area The service is friendly, even from security or parking attendants. Helpful too. Service is also fast, complete set. From feeling okay. I ordered Nasi Ulam and Madurese spiced rice. The Nasi Ulam is really delicious. Soft texture, savory taste and fragrant. Lots of condiments. My only note is, cold chicken only. As for the Madurese spiced rice, its also pretty good, but the black spice taste is too sweet for me. The chili sauce is delicious, fresh spicy. The size of the chicken is also large and soft. Ginger milk is delicious, lots of spices, the milk is also delicious. The advantage of this place is that the space has a vintage and spacious aesthetic. There is indoor AC, indoor non AC, and spacious outdoor. There is even a very large yard + playground. The prayer room is also proper. Clean toilets. Plus there is a bird collection and aquarium, which might be interesting for children.

review_text: On 15 April 22 around 19.00-20.00 WIB, I queued at A&W Lippo Plaza Kramat Jati, I queued at the middle cashier. Cashier serving a woman. The queue is quite long and long. There was only 1 queue in front of me, suddenly the cashier said to move queue, what does that mean??? Is that how your service is to customers?? And the cashier said this while smiling, as if he didnt feel guilty!! After queuing for quite a long time and the queue was still quite long we were asked to move queue??!! I complained via IG DM on 17 Apr 22, and was responded on 18 Apr 22 and asked for my cellphone number and I was just contacted on 21 Apr 22 by a man, and from the way he spoke the man looked like he was new to work, still confused and not demonstrate professionalism at work. My problem was not responded to but instead I asked about the menu at A&W??!! At 16.47 I called back but I didnt pick up because I was on my way, I thought I would be contacted again, but apparently I wasnt. PLEASE IMPROVE YOUR SERVICE, WITHOUT CUSTOMERS YOU ARE NOTHING!!!
review_translated_text: Tanggal 15 Apr 22 sekitar pukul 19.00-20.00 WIB, Saya mengantri di A&W Lippo Plaza Kramat Jati, Saya mengantri di Kasir bagian tengah. Kasir yg melayani seorang Wanita. Antrian cukup lama dan panjang. Tinggal 1 antrian di depan Saya, tiba2 Kasir mengatakan untuk pindah antrian, apa maksudnya ??? Begitukah pelayanan Kalian terhadap Customer ?? Dan kasir menyampaikan hal tersebut sambil tersenyum, seolah tidak merasa bersalah !! Setelah mengantri cukup lama dan antrian masih cukup panjang Kami diminta untuk pindah antrian ??!! Saya complain lewat DM IG tgl 17 Apr 22, dan di respon tgl 18 Apr 22 dan meminta nomor hp Saya dan Saya baru dihubungi di tgl 21 Apr 22 oleh seorang pria, dan dari cara berbicara Pria tersebut seperti orang baru bekerja, masih gelagapan dan tidak menunjukkan ke profesionalitasan dalam bekerja. Permasalahan Saya tidak ditanggapi tetapi malah menanyakan perihal menu yg ada di A& W ??!! Pukul 16.47 menghubungi Saya kembali namun tidak terangkat oleh Saya karena dalam perjalanan, Saya mengira akan dihubungi kembali, namun ternyata tidak. TOLONG PERBAIKI PELAYANAN KALIAN, TANPA CUSTOMER KALIAN BUKAN APA-APA !!!

review_text: good place

Just arrived here to defend from West Bogor and Im really SATISFIED! All the chocolate is not too sweet so you can still taste the basic taste of chocolate! What I ordered is: 1. Triple Chocolate Crepe A soft crepe type with lots of milk chocolate decorations (really a lot) and you can also get the art. For an affordable price, it can be eaten by 2 people. 2. White Chocolate (Beverages) On the menu it says hot, but it turns out you can also order Iced    White chocolate can be said to be delicious (honestly I dont really understand the standard for delicious white chocolate) because the basic taste is more like white chocolate instead of milk. Maybe some people think its still milk, but in terms of taste, you can try it. 3. Signature Dark Choco (Beverage) The reverse version of White Chocolate. It tastes the same as White Choco but the chocolate is stronger. So all in all, if you want to come here, its really worth it. The place is also comfortable, the prices are also not as expensive as the existing cafes
review_translated_text: Baru kesampean ke sini bela2in dr Bogor Barat dan PUAS banget! Semua coklatnya tidak terlalu manis jadi masih bisa merasakan basic taste coklatnya! Yg kupesan adalah: 1. Triple Chocolate Crepe Tipe crepe yg lembut dengan hiasan milk coklat melimpah (beneran banyak) dan seni nya juga dapet. Untuk harga yg affordable bisa dimakan untuk 2 orang. 2. White Chocolate (Beverages) Di menu tertulis hot, ternyata bs req Iced juga    untuk white chocolate bisa dibilang enak (jujur kurang paham standar enak white chocolate) krn basic tastenya lebih terasa coklat putihnya instead of milk. Mungkin sebagian beranggapan tetap itu susu, tp dr segi rasa boleh dicoba. 3. Signature Dark Choco (Beverage) Versi kebalikan White Chocolate. Idem untuk rasanya dengan White Choco tapi lebih kuat aja coklatnya. Jd all over klo mau ke sini worth banget sih. Tempatnya jg nyaman, harganya jg bisa dibilang ga semahal cafe2 yg ada

review_text: The location is in the Cipinang area, East Jakarta, close to Bassura Mall and quite easy to reach. I ordered kabsah rice, kunafa cheese and palm sugar milk coffee. The Kunafa cheese is really fragrant and just the right amount of sweetness, the cheese is also delicious even though its not thick enough. For kabsah rice we will get salad with chili sauce, the rice spices are not strong enough in my opinion so it tastes a bit bland but the taste of the chicken is delicious and the spices also penetrate the meat. Fix will come back again to try the chocolate menu.

Kunafa cheesenya wangi banget dan manisnya pas, cheesenya juga enak walau kurang tebel. Untuk nasi kabsah kita bakal dapet salad sama sambal, rempah nasinya kurang strong menurut gue jd rasanya agak hambar tapi rasa ayamnya enak dan bumbunya juga meresap ke dagingnya. review_text: For those of you who are craving dessert specifically chocolate, try it here. I dont think its too sweet. Yesterday I ordered half moon waffles and signature pancakes, eaten by the four of us and the kids. The portion is just right and doesnt make you tired. But the chocolate here is mixed with milk, so the chocolate doesnt taste bitter, maybe if you like dark chocolate its not suitable. The milkshake is also delicious, doesnt make you tired. Palm sugar iced coffee is also delicious, not the type that contains too much milk. The coffee still tastes great. Must try!
review_translated_text: Buat yang lagi craving for dessert specifically chocolate, cobain deh kesini. Menurutku ga terlalu manis. Kemarin pesen half moon waffle sm signature pancake, dimakan berempat sama anak-anak. Porsinya pas ga bikin eneg. Tapi coklat disini udah campur milk yaa, jadi ga berasa pahit coklatnya, mungkin kalo yang penyuka dark chocolate kurang cocok. Milkshakenya juga enak, ga bikin eneg. Ice coffee gula aren juga enak, bukan tipe yang kebanyakan susu. Kopinya masih berasa banget. Must try!

review_text: Delicious and heart-warning chocolate indulgence Ambience: coffee-shop alike. It was not crowded when i came for lunch. Cute snack and dates stall, as well as the chocolate fountain. Service: so so. Fast response but no greetings. I think the service could be improved more. Menu: mostly chocolate! Heaven for chocolate lover. Salty food are also available, but not too many variations. Mostly arabis food. Taste: Ice signature dark choco (beverage): not my kind of favorite chocolate. Too bitter for me, and i dont like the hint of the after taste. Nasi goreng ayam: delicious! Perfect combination of spices. Middle east kind of food. Signature pancake: rich and delicious flavor of chocolate! Pancake is tender and well cooked. The chocolate topping is so perfect, combined well with the vanilla ice cream. Me likey    they served 3 slices of pancake, so you could share it. Waffle triple chocolate half moon: the chocolate topping is the same with the pancake. Its so perfect. Not too sweet. Just perfect. Waffle is crisp and tender at the same time. You could divide it into 4 big slices, so its possible for sharing. My favorite! Dietary restrictions: Mostly cake and chocolate. No gluten free

The price for the menu is quite expensive, yes, yesterday the bukber package was 53k complete with drink and free takjil. for delicious food, spices and so on. The only thing that was a bit lacking was the service, we had ordered a lesehan and suddenly it was moved to one that wasnt a lesehan on the day of the event. The chairs underneath were also a bit messy, so I didnt clean them straight away, maybe because there were too many tables.

review_text: Great ads campaign all over the mall, and that was what brought us in, the Pastrami Sandwich ads. I love big sandwiches & i Love pastrami, and the word Beast Pastrami says it all, or so i thought. Since it was a limited offer, thus it was not in the menu. To my surprise when it was served, well nothing beast about it. Great marketing skill, however youre missing the disclaimer Picture Is For Illustrative Purpose Only. The overall sandwich flavor itself was good, however fats were not trimmed enough, referring to quite a big chunk chewy & inedible. Service was okay, polite & hospitable servers. Restaurant vibe was warm & welcoming. For the deception i felt, for sure i wont be returning. Quite a pity, rests of the other menu looked quite enticing though.
response_from_owner_text: Dear Mr Anthony, We appreciate your feedback and are sorry to hear about your disappointment with the Pastrami Sandwich. We strive to meet and exceed our customers expectations, and its concerning to learn that we did not meet your expectations on this occasion. We understand the importance of accurately representing our menu items, and we apologize for any confusion caused by the advertisement. Your comments about the sandwichs presentation and taste will be shared with our culinary team for review and improvement. On a positive note, were glad to hear that you found our service polite and hospitable and that you enjoyed the overall ambience of the restaurant. We value your patronage and hope to have the opportunity to regain your trust in the future. Thank you for bringing this to our attention.

review_text: My current favorit

Point Coffee, located inside the convenience store Indomaret, is a hidden gem for coffee lovers. Despite its location, this coffee shop offers a surprisingly pleasant atmosphere with both indoor and ample outdoor seating options. One of the highlights of Point Coffee is the strength of their coffee. If you enjoy a robust and bold cup of joe, this is the place for you. Their coffee is expertly brewed to perfection, delivering a powerful kick that will awaken your senses and give you that much-needed boost of energy. Its a great spot to visit when you need a pick-me-up or a revitalizing break from your daily routine. For those with a sweet tooth, I highly recommend trying their vanilla latte. This personal favorite of mine strikes a perfect balance between the rich, smooth espresso and the sweet, creamy vanilla flavor. The skilled baristas at Point Coffee know how to craft a well-balanced vanilla latte that will leave you satisfied and craving for more. Despite being located inside a convenience store, Point Coffee has managed to create a cozy and comfortable ambiance. The indoor seating area provides a respite from the hustle and bustle of the store, allowing you to enjoy your coffee in a relaxed setting. Additionally, the abundance of outdoor seating is a great option for those who prefer to soak up some fresh air while savoring their cup of coffee. While Point Coffee may not offer the extensive menu or extravagant decor of some standalone coffee shops, its focus on delivering strong and satisfying coffee in a convenient setting is commendable. It provides a quick and reliable caffeine fix for those on the go, without compromising on taste or quality.

One more thing that I appreciate in this restaurant is that they still want to use cutlery to serve the dishes, such as plates and glasses, which means this restaurant is still willing to carry out the activity of washing dishes which is very rare in fast food restaurants. Hopefully the service remains like that, continues to provide proper service, because your customers here are humans, not cats or animals who are given food service using dining paper which is shaped like a place for eating.

review_text: DO NOT RECOMMEND HIGHLY. I had booked for bukber long ago when my turn came and said I hadnt booked yet, even though I had already given money for the down payment for the table. Never mind that when we got there the waiter (guy) was not clear, instead of being given a seat first (even though it was still very empty because he came from 4.30 before fast breaking time) but we were not treated like customers (we were treated like someone who wanted to steal). One of the words from the waiter was We have to know first who is ordering and what their interests are. Whats important is that I want to eat, its none of your business whether the customer comes fasting or not. Waiters should be able to understand how to provide good and correct service. I had to chat back and forth with the IG admin, telephone and all sorts of things just because of their internal miscommunication problems. The employees felt really rude, asking for a power outlet instead of showing them directly but instead the customer told them to look for it themselves. Where the socket is behind the sofa, the customer must also be the one pulling on the sofa. For food at a price that I think is quite pricey and still not enough. Acehnese noodles are okay, shaken noodles are still okay, Spaghetti Bolognese is half cooked, hard and soft. We ordered the takjil package but it turned out that the only additions were dates. That came last, because we had to remind the waiter first if we ordered an iftar package. The place itself is a bit hot, at the front there is only one fan so its not very comfortable. Maybe if you have a big event with up to 10 people it will feel stuffy. Overall, as a condet person, theres no reason to come here. Very tired. I thought that the 4.7 rating on Google yesterday before I came was quite good, but in fact it wasnt.
review_translated_text: GA REKOMEN BANGET. Udah booking untuk bukber jauh hari giliran dateng katanya belom booking, padahal udah kasih uang buat DP meja.  Udahlah sampe sana waiter (cowok) gajelas, bukannya dikasih tempat duduk dulu (padahal masih kosong bgt karna dateng dari jam 4.30 sebelum waktu buka puasa) tapi kita di treat bukan kyk customer (di treat kyk orang mau maling). Salah satu kata2 dari waiternya Kita mesti tau dulu siapa yg mesen dan apa kepentingannya. Lah kepentingannya saya mau makan, urusan customer dateng puasa atau engga juga bukan urusan kalian. Harusnya waiter bisa ngerti buat melakukan service yg baik dan benar. Saya bolak balik mesti ngechat admin IG, telfon dan segala macem hanya karna masalah miskom internal mereka. Karyawannya berasa songong banget, nanya stopkontak bukannya ditunjukkin langsung tapi malah customer suruh nyari sendiri. Mana stop kontak dibelakang sofa harus customer juga yang narik-narik sofanya. Untuk makanan dengan harga yg menurut saya cukup pricey dan masih kurang. Mie aceh oke lah, mie kocok masih oke, Spaghetti Bolognese masaknya setengah mateng, keras dan letis. Kita pesen paket takjil ternyata tambahannya cuma kurma doang. Itupun dateng paling akhir,  karna harus diingetin dulu ke waiternya kalo kita pesen paket buka puasa. Untuk tempatnya sendiri agak panas, dibagian depan cuma ada satu kipas aja jadi ya ga terlalu comfy banget lah. Mungkin kalo buat acara rame sampe 10 orangan bakal terasa pengapnya. Overall sebagai orang condet, ga deh buat dateng kesini. Kapok banget. Dipikir rating 4.7 di google kemarin sebelum saya datang cukup oke, nyatanya tidak.

review_text: This is my first time eating at Platinum. Ordered sirloin steak... when it arrived, it turned out it was a hot plate model that had to be cooked first like a pep**er lu*ch. I think it will immediately become holy  . What Im confused about is that there are fries there that are already cooked (the color is already a nice golden brown), along with green beans, carrots and corn that look like theyve been boiled. Then why do you put it on the hot plate too? It will cook and then overcook, aka it will burn hahaha As for the steak, it wasnt tender enough :(. Tbh, I cut the sirloin and it took a lot of effort, to the point where it was dry (maybe because I was pregnant, I got irritated easily). Yes, you can imagine how rich the steak would be because just cutting it made it dry like that hahaha. As for the sauce, I think its a little salty. Then for drinks, I just ordered mango smoothies because it reduces caffeine for pregnant women. And it turns out its really muaniiss, I dont know if its sweet from the mango, or the sugar, or... from the sweetened condensed milk (?) But I dont think its from the mango, as sweet as the mango is, it doesnt seem like that much. But its delicious, but its really sweet, please.

Kirain yg langsung jadi kaya holy . Yg saya bingung, disitu kan ada kentang goreng yg emang base nya udah mateng (warna nya udah cakep golden brown gitu), sama buncis, wortel, jagung yg keliatannya udah direbus gitu. Terus kenapa ditaro juga di hot plate nya yak, kan jadinya ikut kemasak terus jadi overcook alias gosong wkwk Untuk steak nya kurang empuk :(. Tbh, saya motong sirloin nya perlu effort banget, sampe keringetan (mungkin karna lagi hamil juga sih jadi gampang gerah). Ya bisa dibayangin lah ya steak nya kaya gimana karna motong nya aja sampe keringetan gitu wkwk. Untuk sauce nya, menurut saya keasinan dikit. Terus untuk minumannya, saya pesen mango smoothies aja karna ngurangin kafein buat bumil. Dan ternyata muaniiss bangeett wkwk gak tau itu manis dari mangga nya kah, atau gula nya kah, atau... dari susu kental manis (?) Tapi kayanya kalo dari mangga nya nggak deh, se manis2 nya mangga kayanya gak sampe segitunya. Tapi enak sih, tapi kemanisan banget plis.

review_text: Location on the 2nd floor of Plaza Atrium Senen Near the elevator, near Miniso

Platinum in the atrium plaza is located on the 2nd floor.. Visited here during fasting last Tuesday. So at Platinum we dont accept bookings during fast breaking time. Only those whose personnel are complete can be let in. As a result, even though we were B5 and there were 3 new arrivals, we were brave enough to say that everything was complete. We were led to a table with 4 chairs. But it turned out that the 1 empty chair was immediately taken back by the lady. The lady said that next time someone comes, they wont promise a seat because thats the system. But luckily when our 2 friends came later, the waiters there still didnt bother looking for extra chairs After being a bit confused about what menu to choose, I finally decided to order the Hainanese spicy and sour chicken because I saw that it had tofu and it looked fresh from the picture. When you taste it, its not bad. The Hainanese rice is delicious, the tofu is delicious, the chicken is crunchy but the sauce is more dominant in sourness, it doesnt feel spicy at all. The only vegetable there is a leaf of mustard greens in the broth.. Theres nothing special about the Spiderman menu, except the usual sausages and French fries that are sold packaged in supermarkets.
review_translated_text: Platinum di atrium plaza ini terletak d lantai 2.. Berkunjung kemari saat bukber hri selasa lalu. Jaadi di platinum ini ga terima bookingan tampat selama waktu buka puasa. Siapa yg personilnya udah lengkap baru bisa dikasih masuk. Alhasil walaupun kami b5 dan yang baru datang 3 kami nekat aja bilang udah lengkap semua. Diantarkanlah kaami ke meja dengan 4 kursi. Tapi ternyata 1 kursi yg kosong itu langsung di ambil lagi sm mbaknya. Mbaknya bilang kl nanti ada yg datang lagi, mereka gbs janjiin kursi krn memang sistemnya begitu. Tp untungnya saat 2 teman kami datang belakangan, pelayan2 disana masih mau direpotkan untuk mencarikan kursi tambahan Setelah agak bingung mau pilih menu apa akhirnya memutuskan pesan ayam asam pedas hainan karena lihat ada tofunya dan kelihatan segar aja dari gambarnya. Saaat dicicip, lumayan lah ya. Nasi hainannya enak, tofunya enak, ayamnya crunchy tp untuk saucenya lebih dominan ke asamnya, pedasnya tidak terasa sama sekali. Sayurnya cuma terdapat selembar sawi di dalam kuah kaldu.. Kalau menu spiderman sih ga ada istimewanya cm sosis dan french fries biasa yg dijual kemasan di supermarket2 gitu.

review_text: The food here is quite good, the service is quite good, but for some reason it occurred to me how come Bakmi Naga can rent a place for its business location with a diameter that is small enough so that the distance between the tables is close to each other. Its not that I dont like interacting with other humans, its just that when I come here next to people eating, their conversations are very exciting and their voices can be heard very clearly at the table next to where I sit, because the shape of the area is just a box and then filled with chairs and tables that are next to each other. close by. My suggestion would be better if you move to a bigger location so that visitors will be more comfortable eating here. But this is just a suggestion, if it cant be done, thats okay.

review_text: One of the classic places to eat in Darrah Permata Hijau. We ordered casio noodles and shrimp spring rolls. The capcay rice is delicious and you can order the rice type again, such as egg fried rice, so it smells good. The noodles are not our taste, the taste is a bit lacking. You must order the shrimp spring rolls when you come here because they are delicious and fragrant.
review_translated_text: Salah satu tempat makan klasik di darrah permata hijau. Kita pesan nasi capcay bakmi casio dan lumpia udang. Nasi capcaynya enak dan boleh banget untuk dipesan ulang tipe nasinya sepeti nasi goreng telur jadi wangi. Untuk bakminya bukan selera kami dimana rasanya agak kurang. Lumpia udangnya harus dipesan kalau kesini karena inj enak dan wangi.

review_text: This restaurant is famous for the consistency of taste and quality of its dishes. Every time I come to this restaurant I always order Bakmi Casio, Nasi Cap Cay, and Shrimp Lumpia. The texture of the curly noodles is just right. The portion is enough for one person. Add chili sauce or pepper to add to the enjoyment of the taste of the noodles. Meanwhile, the portion for capcay rice is quite large and can even be shared between two people. The fried spring rolls are very delicious, you have to try this menu.
review_translated_text: Restoran ini terkenal dengan konsistensi rasa dan kualitas masakannya. Setiap kali datang ke restoran ini saya selalu pesan Bakmi Casio, Nasi Cap cay, dan Lumpia Udang. Tekstur bakmi keritingnya pas. Porsinya cukup untuk satu orang. Ditambah sambal atau lada untuk menambah kenikmatan dari rasa bakmi nya. Sedangkan untuk nasi capcay nya porsinya cukup besar bahkan bisa disharing untuk dua orang. Lumpia gorengnya sangat enak, kalian harus mencoba menu ini.

Bakmi Permata classic restaurant. Came here for lunch for two of us. We ordered plain mushroom noodles, cap cay rice, and hot plate kangkung (beef). Clean place, friendly service, and old school music The texture of the noodles is like in the photo, the elasticity of the noodles is just right, the mixture of vegetables and mushrooms is just right. It seems that if you reduce the amount of pepper it would be better. Portions are sufficient. Cap Cay rice is delicious, portion is sufficient. Kale hot plate (beef) is delicious. The tauco taste doesnt dominate. The beef is tender, the kale looks fresh. Portions are sufficient. Parking: Parking lot is available in front of restaurant. However, bigger parking space is available nearby (in front of shopping center).

review_text: One of the cafes which is still relatively new in the Kalimalang area. The building is easy to find from the road because it is quite large, parking space is somewhat limited for cars compared to the capacity of the place. Its a bit difficult to find parking at busy times. The food is quite delicious and affordable. The place is also cozy for chatting. The distance between tables is not too narrow so it is still comfortable to chat. Here the visitor capacity is large enough so it can be used as a place for parties. And whats unique is that there is an outdoor rooftop restaurant here too.
review_translated_text: Salah satu cafe yang masi agak tergolong agak baru di daerah kalimalang. Bangunan mudah ditemukan dari jalan karena cukup besar, space parkir agak terbatas untuk mobil dibandingkan kapasitas tempatnya. Agak sulit untuk cari parkir di jam2 ramai. Untuk makanan cukup enak dan terjangkau. Tempatnya juga cozy untuk ngobrol. Jarak antar meja tidak terlalu sempit sehingga masi nyaman untuk ngobrol. Disini kapasitas pengunjung cukup banuak sehingga bisa dijadikan tempat untuk pesta. Dan uniknya ada rooftop resto yang outdoor juga disini.

review_text: Elegant and comfortable interior design. If you come here in the afternoon, you must go to the rooftop because the sunset is beautiful. The menu is quite complete, available coffee, non-coffee, fresh drinks etc. For food, rice, pasta, platters, etc. are available. I tried the mozzarella croquette & purple star. Both are delicious, the price is a bit pricey but I think its worth it with the ambience, service and all the facilities

Menu cukup lengkap, tersedia kopi, non kopi, minuman seger dll. untuk makanan tersedia nasi, pasta, platter, dll. aku coba mozarella croket & purple star. Keduanya enak, harganya emang agak pricey tapi menurutku worth it dengan ambience, pelayanan, dan semua fasilitasnya

review_text: I often pass by every time I get home from work, only to arrive because there is a bukber event. For delicious food and recommended. The cromboloni are delicious too. The service from the waiters is also very friendly. Also a good place to chat One thing that needs to be improved is parking. I got on a motorbike, when I came out I saw the front motorbike myself, I paid 2 thousand and it was my turn because I didnt have 2 thousand I paid 5 thousand, the parking attendant went to the back, thought he wanted to take change, but apparently he didnt. After being charged the change he said the parking fee was 5 thousand for the motorbike. Honestly, Im a little upset inside. Because there are no tariffs listed, the position is weak. Management should display the parking price on a board or provide tickets with the parking fee stated. So that everything is clear Parking: Its best to write down the parking fee. So that there are no lies Wheelchair accessibility: Elevator available

Saya naik motor, saat keluar melihat sendiri motor depan saya bayar 2rb dan giliran saya karena tidak ada 2rb saya bayar 5rb, tukang parkirnya pergi ke belakang, kirain mau ambil kembalian,ternyata tidak. Setelah ditagih kembalian bilangnya biaya parkirnya 5rb untuk motor. Jujur agak dongkol dalam hati. Karena tidak ada tarif yang tertera, jadi posisinya lemah. Sebaiknya manajemen menampilkan harga parkir di papan atau diberikan karcis yang tertera tarif parkir. Agar semuanya jelas Parking: Sebaiknya dituliskan tarif parkir. review_text: Travellers! Find Cafe Aesthetic in X-Malang!! So, when I went back to work yesterday, I was on the side of the road when I saw a coffee shop on the main road in Kalimalang! Just stopped by for a coffee while waiting out the afternoon traffic jam here. It turns out that this coffeeshop has been renovated, its even more beautiful and aesthetic... especially the rooftop Aselikkk, really cozy place. The space is outside and the first floor is used for parking. There is Velvet parking too. This Coffeeshop is really cool! You really have to stop by here. If you have plans to hold an event in 2023, this is the place. Because there are 4 floors, the space is really spacious and comfortable. Nah, dont want a lot of spills, just watch the reels! Stop by gaskuyy.. @coveragecoffeeandeatery Kalimalang Jl. Admiral Malahayati, Cipinang Muara, East Jakarta 10.00 -24.00 WIB Starting from 50 thousand

Mampir dulu dah sembari ngopi sambil nunggu kemacetan sore daerah sini. Ternyata coffeeshop ini habis direnovasi, tambah cantik dan estetik yaaa.. apalagi Rooftopnya Aselikkk, cozy banget tempatnya. Space nya luar dan udah gitu lantai 1 nya dipake buat parkir. Ada Velvet parkingnya juga. Keren banget sih ini lah Coffeeshop! Kalian wajib banget nyempetin mampir kesini ya. Kalo mau ada rencana bikin event di tahun 2023 disini sih tempatnya. Karena ada 4 lantai yang spacenya bener-bener luas dan nyaman. Dahlah, gak mau banyak spill, tonton aja yak reelsnya! Mampir gaskuyy.. @coveragecoffeeandeatery Kalimalang Jl. Laksamana Malahayati, Cipinang Muara, Jaktim 10.00 -24.00 WIB Mulai dari 50ribuan

review_text: Facilities and comfort: The facilities in this restaurant are quite good, there are also chairs for toddlers. And comfortable too because the vibe and atmosphere are very authentic and typical of Indonesia and make visitors feel comfortable. Lightning is right and the architecture is also good, visitors feel comfortable Food: The taste of the food is good, but still the same as other restaurants, the taste is just ordinary. However, from the way it is cooked, the spices are not overdone and just right on the tongue, the beef rendang and beef satay are also not hard and tender. 5 stars for the chef. The food plating is also good. But unfortunately, in my opinion, its not worth it because the price is quite expensive and the taste is the same as the others Drinks: The drinks are delicious and different from the others. The plating is nice and beautiful to look at. Unfortunately they may be a little more expensive than they should be. Sweet tea alone is 17 thousand? and avocado coffee juice 49 thousand? Maybe it could be lowered a little to make it more affordable for customers. But most of all, the taste is still delicious and fits the tongue Service: The service here and how the waiters serve their customers is still somewhat lacking. Customers have to wait a long time for the food and drinks they order. Not only that, many waiters are confused about delivering food to their customers. For example, I, who didnt order bakwan, was suddenly given bakwan, and there were many incidents where the waiter was confused about delivering the food. Maybe on another occasion it can be improved again Atmosphere: The atmosphere is authentic with warm colored lights. Its comfortable on the eyes, and the architecture is also nice and instagrammable. Overall there are still good and bad parts, maybe on another occasion the things that are lacking can be improved... Kid-friendliness: The restaurant is child friendly, there are special chairs for toddlers
review_translated_text: Fasilitas dan kenyamanan: Fasilitas di resto ini cukup bagus, ada juga kursi untuk balita. Dan nyaman juga karena vibe dan atmospherenya sangat otentik dengan khas indonesia dan membuat pengunjung merasa nyaman. Lightning sudah pas dan arsitekturnya juga bagus, pengunjung jadi merasa nyaman Makanan: Rasa makanannya enak, tapi tetep sama seperti resto lainnya, rasanya biasa saja. Namun dari cara memasaknya, bumbunya tidak over dan pas di lidah, daging rendang dan daging sate sapi nya juga tidak keras dan empuk. Bintang 5 untuk chefnya. Plating makanannya juga bagus. Namun sayangnya menurut saya kurang worth it dengan harganya yang lumayan mahal dengan rasa yang sama seperti lainnya Minuman: Minumannya enak dan beda dari yang lainnya. Platingnya bagus dan indah dipandang. Sayangnya harganya mungkin sedikit lebih mahal daripada yang seharusnya. Teh manis saja 17 ribu? dan jus kopi alpukat 49 ribu? Mungkin bisa diturunkan sedikit supaya lebih terjangkau bagi pelanggan. Namun terlebih dari semuanya itu, rasanya tetap enak dan pas di lidah Pelayanan: Pelayanan disini dan bagaimana pelayan melayani pelanggannya masih terbilang kurang. Pelanggan harus menunggu agak lama makanan dan minuman yang dipesan. Bukan hanya itu, banyak pelayan yang bingung dalam mengantarkan makanannya kepada pelanggannya. Contoh saya yang tidak memesan bakwan tiba-tiba dikasih bakwan, dan banyak kejadian pelayan kebingungan dalam mengantar makanan. Mungkin di lain kesempatan bisa ditingkatkan lagi Suasana: Suasananya otentik dengan warna lampu yang warm. Membuat nyaman di mata, dan arsitekturnya juga bagus dan instagrammable. Overall masih terdapat bagian yang bagus dan kurang, mungkin di lain kesempatan bisa ditingkatkan hal-hal yang kurangnya.. Kid-friendliness: Restonya ramah anak, terdapat kursi khusus untuk balita

review_text: From the moment I stepped into Rempah Bistro, I was enveloped in a world of aromatic delights. The ambiance perfectly blends elegance and comfort, ideal for both casual and special dining. The menu showcases the richness of Indonesian cuisine. Each dish, especially the Beef Rendang and Gado-Gado, was a testament to the careful blend of spices and fresh ingredients. The rendangs tender meat and the gado-gados refreshing mix with creamy, spicy peanut sauce were standouts. The commitment to high-quality ingredients is evident in every bite. The service is also remarkable, with attentive and knowledgeable staff. Rempah Bistro at Pondok Indah Mall 2 is a must-visit for authentic Indonesian cuisine at its best. Highly recommended for a memorable dining experience.

This restaurant is chaotic. There are lots of staff but they dont know how to serve customers. We ordered rice and side dishes, a total of 6 side dishes. About 25 minutes later the rice and rendang came. Well wait and see if the other side dishes dont come. About 10 minutes later the oxtail soup came. We were hungry so we immediately started eating because we thought the other 4 side dishes we ordered would come soon. But until we finished eating the rendang and soup, the other side dishes hadnt arrived yet. We have to ask several times, where are the other side dishes? And the restaurant was quiet at that time so the service should have been faster. And the rice and side dishes should come at the same time. Not rice first and 1-2 foods then the other food only came 30 - 40 minutes later. Im confused about what this concept is. All food should be taken out at the same time so you can eat it all instead of coming out one by one over a long period of time. Long story short, we are very emotional and annoyed. Appetite is lost. As soon as the other food arrived, we were no longer interested in eating so we had to take it away. This is not a cheap restaurant, the three of us ate there for around 1 million. with service like that, really not worth it. So Im tired of not wanting to go there anymore. Food taste is also 5 out of 10. Really disappointed.

Kita sudah lapar jadi langsung mulai makan karena kita pikir 4 lauk lain nya yang kita order akan datang segera. March 28, my friends and I planned to have bukber in Leko Gancit. Because honestly I miss their rib penyet. At 5 oclock we arrived at the restaurant. Disclm: On the 27th I tried calling to make a reservation but the officer said you couldnt RSVP at Leko, you had to come in person. When my friends and I arrived, we asked if there were still tables available for 7 people. The officer said there was, and we were directed to the table, we were also told not to leave the table. We sat for about 10-15 minutes at the table while waiting for the still long drum and selecting the menu to open. Suddenly female officer 1 came who asked us to move from the chair because SAID OUR SEAT WAS ALREADY IN RSPV. It needs to be underlined that we tried rspv on day-1 by phone and we were not allowed to rspv, I told the lady about this. Then she left. 10 minutes later 2 female officers came who pushed us away firmly. That this table has been rspved by their OFFICE. Disappointed.? Clear. Because it was already 5.20 and we had to look for another restaurant that was available for 7 people. The reason is that the table has been RSPVed even though I previously confirmed RSPV, it says it cant. Its sad that we were kicked out precisely because our table had already been RSPVed. Strange!!
response_from_owner_text: Dear Mrs. Dessi, We apologize for the inconvenience caused. After we investigated with the waiter/waitress on duty on the shift, there was miscommunication and delivery errors. We had provided an alternative table for 7 people, but it was rejected. We would like to respectfully contact Ms Dessi, apologize and take responsibility directly, can you provide a contact number that can be contacted via WA to our number: +62 812-8049-1281. Thank you, Miss Dessi. Always healthy greetings.

Perlu di garis bawahi kami sudah coba rspv h-1 by phone dan kami tidak boleh rspv, saya sempat bilang ke mba nya prihaal ini. Lalu mbanya pergi. 10 menit kemudia datang petugas wanita 2 yg mengusir kami dengan tegas. Bahwa meja ini sudah di rspv oleh OFFICE mereka . Kecewa.? Jelas. Karena itu sudah 5.20 dan kami harus cari resto lain yang available untuk 7 orang. Alasan table sudah di rspv padahal saya sebelumnya sudah konfirasi untuk rspv katanya ga bisa. review_text: After the meeting, I wanted to go to the office again, but suddenly I had to go to Gancit, even though I was very hungry. Plus 2 stir-fries, an omelet and bubbling hot black tea. Use soft white rice of course. Thats damned rice I swear. Makes it really delicious to eat without waiting. Thank you, Warung Lekko. You have made us happy with your food and service.

Ditambah 2 tumisan, telur dadar, dan teh hitam panas menggelegak. Pake nasi putih pulen tentunya. Itu nasi jahanam sumpah. Bikin makan gak kelar2 sangking enaknya. Makasih ya Warung Lekko. Sudah bikin kami senang karena makanan dan layanan kalian.

review_text: Cool! Its not difficult to find this place, it is located in one of the shophouses on the side of the main road lined with the Jatinegara Premier Hospital right next to Holland Bakery. They make good use of the space, on the terrace there is a sitting table lined with potted plants (this is suitable for afternoons and evenings, because during the day it is quite hot), inside there is a non-smoking room, and another room for a smoking area, and it is air conditioned. Served by two cool young men in their 20s as Baristas and also Waiters, this place is often visited by office employees who are taking a break or coming home from work to gentlemen who are just spending time unwinding or chatting about work with colleagues. I myself came here while working on my laptop, the downside is that I couldnt use the Wi-Fi when I came here, but it was quite conducive and quite for working. The menu is quite varied, from coffee, non-coffee, snacks to heavy meals, and the prices are really affordable. Here you can enjoy one cup of coffee for 20K and it tastes delicious. Will definitely come here again!
review_translated_text: Cool! Tidak sulit menemukan tempat ini, berada di salah satu ruko pinggir jalan raya jejeran rumah sakit premiere Jatinegara persis di sebelah Holland Bakery. Mereka memanfaatkan space dengan baik, di teras ada meja duduk yang dipagari tanaman2 pot (ini cocok buat sore ke malam hari, karena kalau siang lumayan panas), di dalam ada ruang non smoking, dan satu ruangan lagi buat smoking area, dan ber AC. Dilayani oleh dua pemuda kece umur 20an sebagai Barista dan juga Pramusaji, tempat ini banyak ditongkrongi oleh pegawai kantor yang sedang istirahat atau pulang kerja hingga bapak2 yang sekadar menghabiskan waktu untuk melepas lelah atau ngobrol membahas pekerjaan dengan kolega. Saya sendiri kemari sambil kerja buka laptop, minusnya adalah wi-fi tidak dapat digunakan saat saya kemari, namun cukup kondusif and quite untuk bekerja. Menu cukup bervariasi mulai dari coffee, non coffee, snack hingga makanan berat juga ada, dan harga nya masuk kantong banget. Disini kmu bisa menikmati satu cup coffee seharga 20K dan rasanya enak. Pastinya akan kemari lagi!

review_text: The place is good, the indoor and outdoor seating areas are sufficient, the prices are okay, there is also parking. I regularly get my hair cut here because its close to home, usually with Mas Edo. Great, never disappointed. The standard price for a haircut is IDR 50k, if you use a wash, its IDR 60k. I used to like drinking coffee when I was waiting or hanging out with friends, but in the end I never ordered coffee again. The coffee needs to be improved further, especially espresso based. Baristas should be given sufficient training or product knowledge, especially regarding coffee. I have ordered cappuccinos many times here and always been disappointed with the milk frothing. Either way, the foam isnt right, the temperature is too high, and if possible, dont use UHT. I think the preparation of employees abilities in F&B can be improved further. Service is always okay. Its just a shame that the product is lacking. Hopefully this will be constructive input. Thanks

review_text: Cemara DBalcony Cafe & Coffee has two areas, namely the indoor and outdoor areas. The indoor area is quite spacious and comfortable. The outdoor area is suitable for relaxing and enjoying the fresh air. Menu: Cemara DBalcony Cafe & Coffee provides a variety of menus, ranging from heavy foods such as fried rice and chicken noodles, to light snacks such as toast and fried bananas. There are also various beverage options, such as coffee, tea and juice. Prices: The prices of food and drinks at Cemara DBalcony Cafe & Coffee are quite affordable. You can enjoy food and drinks with prices starting from IDR 15,000 - IDR 50,000. Service: The service at Cemara DBalcony Cafe & Coffee is quite friendly and alert. Your order will be delivered quickly and the staff is always ready to help if you need anything. Excess: Comfortable and modern atmosphere Beautiful natural scenery Diverse menu An affordable price Friendly service Lack: Can be busy during rush hours Cemara DBalcony Cafe & Coffee is a suitable place to hang out with friends or family. The comfortable atmosphere, beautiful views and varied menu make it the right choice to relax and enjoy your free time.
review_translated_text: Cemara DBalcony Cafe & Coffee memiliki dua area, yaitu area indoor dan outdoor. Area indoornya cukup luas dan nyaman. Area outdoornya cocok untuk bersantai dan menikmati udara segar. Menu: Cemara DBalcony Cafe & Coffee menyediakan berbagai macam menu, mulai dari makanan berat seperti nasi goreng dan mie ayam, hingga camilan ringan seperti roti bakar dan pisang goreng. Ada juga berbagai macam pilihan minuman, seperti kopi, teh, dan jus. Harga: Harga makanan dan minuman di Cemara DBalcony Cafe & Coffee tergolong cukup terjangkau. Anda bisa menikmati makanan dan minuman dengan harga mulai dari Rp15.000 - Rp50.000. Pelayanan: Pelayanan di Cemara DBalcony Cafe & Coffee cukup ramah dan sigap. Pesanan Anda akan diantarkan dengan cepat dan stafnya selalu siap membantu jika Anda membutuhkan sesuatu. Kelebihan: Suasana yang nyaman dan modern Pemandangan alam yang indah Menu yang beragam Harga yang terjangkau Pelayanan yang ramah Kekurangan: Bisa ramai pada jam-jam sibuk Cemara DBalcony Cafe & Coffee adalah tempat yang cocok untuk nongkrong bersama teman atau keluarga. Suasananya yang nyaman, pemandangannya yang indah, dan menu yang beragam menjadikannya pilihan yang tepat untuk bersantai dan menikmati waktu luang.

review_text: I ordered at 8pm, it was already past breaking time, there were lots of empty seats, I ordered a package of grilled chicken 52k, cok fried rice 40k, basil chili sauce 9k. He said there was no spoon! Is that the time to answer? We complained and then waited until the spoon was finally brought! If a restaurant runs out of spoons, if youre packing grilled chicken, its okay to use your hands, this is oily fried rice, and sorry, it doesnt taste enough, the rice is soggy. The cashier and waitress didnt connect and threw each other at each other, angry at each other because they missed an order. Theres a lack of management.

Im already looking forward to returning to sample some of their other enticing drinks from the menu. One thing to note is that the cafe isnt very conspicuous; its tucked away on the second floor. But for a delicious and more budget-friendly coffee option compared to Starbucks, its definitely worth the find.

review_text: Bude Pakde Coffee The small, Javanese-style coffeeshop gives a cozy and homey impression. There are several places to sit outside, even though it is outdoor, it is still comfortable and cool because there are quite shady trees. For a fairly complete menu, I ordered the Manies Ireng mocktail here, 23k, this is a combination of espresso, lychee syrup and tonic water, its fresh and delicious. Apart from that, I also ordered Telang Jiwa, 26k, this is a combination of telang flowers, lemon and soda, the color is beautiful blue and the taste is fresh.
review_translated_text: Kopi Bude Pakde Coffeeshop mungil dan bergaya khas Jawa memberikan kesan cozy dan homey. Ada beberapa tempat duduk di outdoor, meski outdoor namun masih nyaman dan adem karena ada pohon lumayan rindang. Untuk menu cukup lengkap, saya kesini pesan mocktail Manies Ireng, 23k, ini merupakan perpaduan espresso, sirup leci dan air tonic, ini segar dan nikmat. Selain itu Saya juga pesan Telang Jiwa, 26k, ini perpaduan bunga telang, lemon dan soda, warnanya biru cantik dan rasanya segar.

review_text: This is the second time I have stopped by Kopi Bude Pakde. From the first visit, I fell in love with the atmosphere. The place is small and a bit hidden, so its really suitable to be called Condets hidden gem. I really like it because the atmosphere is calm, not noisy, shady because there are lots of trees and lots of breeze. Its really comfortable to have morning coffee or afternoon coffee here. Even now they have a 2nd floor area so there is more seating and capacity. On the 2nd floor you can get beautiful shadows, so those who take photos will definitely like the lighting on the 2nd floor. Here I ordered Iced Kopi Kasmaran and Iced Lychee Yakult. For the iced milk coffee, I requested less sugar, so the coffee is more dominant, and for the lychee yakult ice, I think it tastes a bit sweet, maybe because I requested the ice separately, so the composition wasnt quite right because I didnt know the proper amount of ice cubes. Overall, this is my favorite coffeeshop in Condet
review_translated_text: Ini kali kedua aku mampir ke Kopi Bude Pakde. Dari kunjungan pertama pun udah dibuat jatuh cinta dengan suasananya. Tempatnya mungil dan agak tersembunyi jadi cocok banget kalau dibilang hidden gem Condet. Aku suka banget karena suasananya yang tenang, nggak berisik, teduh karena banyak pohon dan banyak angin sepoi-sepoinya. Betah banget kalau ngopi pagi atau ngopi sore disini. Sekarang pun mereka punya area lantai 2 jadi tempat duduk dan daya tampungnya lebih banyak. Di lantai 2 ini bisa dapet shadow cantik, jadi buat yang foto-foto pasti suka sama pencahayaan di lantai 2 ini. Disini aku order Es Kopi Kasmaran dan Es Lychee Yakult. Kalau es kopi susunya aku req less sugar jadi kopinya lebih dominan dan untuk es lychee yakult menurutku rasanya agak kemanisan, mungkin karena aku req esnya terpisah kali yaa jadi komposisinya kurang pas karena aku ngga tau takaran es batu yang seharusnya. For my taste, the chocolate ice is sweet, maybe because I dont like sweet, for the kebab pizza (forgot what its called on the menu) its not bad... the outside of the kebab skin is inside with bolognese sauce, the price is 25 thousand. review_text: Try it at the Jatinegara branch, This is the type of coffee place that only thinks about aesthetics. Ordered a mocktail which was said to be creamy, served in a champagne glass, the portion was small, I didnt see the process of making it, it looked like it was shaken with ice to make it cold, then poured into a glass, served with whip cream which had been added with berry syrup. The price is 38000+tax. Looks okay 5 stars, taste? Just taste sugar. A few times while listening to the location, there was a large coffee grinder visible from the main road, there was a crowd, my expectations were quite high if the coffee was good. But when it arrived, it was unexpectedly super disappointing. Then there is the beef sei menu with rice, this is just bacon and egg plus sei-style condiments. Of the 3 items I ordered, only the food was okay, who doesnt like bacon and eggs, right? The place is quite artistically designed, there is a small air-conditioned room where all the guests gather at that point during the day, dont expect privacy here, everyone in the room will be able to hear what is being said here clearly. Luckily there werent any noisy guests in the room. The barista tried to say thank you to let the guests go, but sorry I was in a bad mood and got a drink that didnt feel worth the price. Oh yes, dont be surprised if this place seems busy even though the menu isnt good. Because the owner is an artist. Recommended? Nope! Will you come back again? Nope! OK, leave a review at this branch first, maybe later it will be moved to the Jatinegara branch if its already on the map. Hopefully there will be improvements in taste in the future. (Im sure this is not the baristas fault but the recipes fault regarding taste)
review_translated_text: Nyobain di cabang jatinegara, Ini tipe tempat ngopi yg super mikirin estetika aja. Mesen mocktail yg katanya creamy disajikan dalam gelas champagne, porsi kecil saya ga liat proses pembuatannya sepertinya di shake dengan es supaya dingin lalu dituang dalam gelas, disajikan dengan whip cream yg sudah ditambahkam sirup berry. Harganya 38000+tax. Penampilan oke bintang 5, rasa? Rasa gula aja. Sekian kali lewat nyimak di lokasi ada grinder kopi besar terlihat dr jalan raya, ada keramaian, ekspektasi gw cukup tinggi kalo kopinya enak. Tapi pas dateng diluar dugaan super mengecewakan. Lalu ada menu sei sapi dengan nasi, ini cuma bacon and egg ditambah condiment ala sei aja. Dari 3 item yg saya order cuma makanannya yg yah okelah, siapa juga yang ga doyan bacon and egg ya kan? Tempat di desain lumayan artistik, ada 1 ruangan kecil ber ac dimana semua tamunya berkumpul di titik tsb saat siang, jangan harap privasi disini, apa yg dibicarakan disini semua orang dalam ruangan tsb akan bisa ikut nyimak dengan jelas. Untung tamunya ga ada yg berisik di ruangan tsb. Baristanya berusaha say thank you melepas kepergian tamunya, tapi sorry udah keburu bad mood dapet minuman yg rasa ga sebanding dengan harga. Oh ya jangan heran kalo tempat ini sepintas rame sekalipun menunya ga oke. Soalnya ownernya artis. Recomended? Nope! Akan balik lagi? Nope! Ok nitip review di cabang ini dulu, mungkin nanti akan dipindahkan ke cabang jatinegara kalo sudah ada di map. Moga2 ada perbaikan rasa ke depannya. (soal rasa saya yakin ini bukan kesalahan barista tapi resepnya)

review_text: The second house from Tuan Tanah (first house in Pondok Bambu). The location is on the side of the road, but I havent seen a sign so its easy to miss it. There is motorbike parking, car parking is at the very edge. So far, homies place... there is indoor and outdoor, the outdoor is cool. The drink ordered Kara Hara and Senandung Masa. Both are basic mocktails with a flowery sensation. Kara Hara includes coffee (espresso + syrup, I think). Delicious & fresh but not special. Hum Masa is unique, it has a bright sour taste, maybe lemon, but it has a flowery & spice aroma, I think. Yes, if youre not used to it, you might not like it. The fries are okay, not bad.
review_translated_text: Ruma kedua dari TuanTanah (rumah pertama di Pondok Bambu). Lokasinya dipinggir jalan, cuma saya belom liat ada signnya jadi rawan terlewat. Parkiran motor ada, parkir mobil ya di pinggirnya paling. So far tempatnya homie  ada indoor dan outdoor, outdoornya adem. Minumnya pesan Kara Hara sama Senandung Masa. Keduanya basic mocktail dengan flowery sensation. Kara Hara dia masuknya coffee (espresso + syrup buan kayaknya). Enak & seger tapi not to special. Senandung Masa dia unik, ada rasa asam yang bright mungkin lemon tapi ada aroma flowery & rempah kayaknya. Ya kalo ga biasa mungkin bisa jadi kurang suka. Kentang goreng oke lumayan.

review_text: Jatinegara Landlord The newest branch of TuanTanah is located in Jatinegara, the gmaps position is very precise and the location is also on the side of the road so it is very easy to find. The front facade is attractive with an unfinished concept that looks unique and classic. For a fairly complete menu, I ordered their signature mocktail here, namely Arunima, 38k, a combination of coffee shots, spices, macadamia and cream, the taste is sweet, fresh and creamy, the color is beautiful. Since its still a soft opening, there are still promos, so you can order Sei Sapi Sambal Matah, 55k and Iced Kopi Susu Tuan Tanah Rempah, 30k. Everything is delicious, but its a shame I didnt have time to take photos.
review_translated_text: TuanTanah Jatinegara Cabang terbaru dari TuanTanah yang letaknya di Jatinegara, posisi gmaps nya sangat tepat dan lokasi juga di pinggir jalan jadi sangat mudah ditemukan. Facade depannya menarik dengan konsep unfinished terkesan unik dan klasik. Untuk menu lumayan lengkap, Saya kesini pesan signature mocktail mereka yaitu Arunima, 38k, perpaduan coffee shot, spice, macadamia dan cream, rasanya manis segar dan creamy, warnanya pun cantik. Berhubung masih soft opening masih dapat promo jadi bisa pesan Sei Sapi Sambal Matah, 55k dan Es Kopi susu tuan Tanah Rempah, 30k. Semuanya enak cuma sayang gak sempat difoto.

review_text: Congratulations @tuantanah.idn for the opening of second home at Jatinegara! . Located in a classic house left by @atiqahhasiholans grandfather, this house has now been converted into a beautiful coffee shop. The heritage atmosphere still feels very strong here, attractive classic details combined with rustic touches make every corner of this place look aesthetic. . The seating area is quite spacious, there is an indoor area which is suitable for working and a semi-outdoor area which is quite cool and comfortable for hanging out. A variety of menus are served here, starting from snacks, meals and beverages, there are also coffee, non-coffee and mocktails which are of course fresh and delicious.
review_translated_text: Congratulations @tuantanah.idn for the opening of second home at Jatinegara! . Berlokasi di sebuah rumah klasik peninggalan kakek dari kak @atiqahhasiholan, kini rumah ini dialihfungsikan menjadi sebuah coffee shop yang cantik. Suasana heritage masih terasa sangat kental disini, detail-detail klasik yang menarik dipadukan dengan sentuhan rustic membuat setiap sudut tempat ini terlihat estetik. . Seating areanya cukup spacious, ada indoor area yang cocok untuk jadi tempat kerja dan semi-outdoor area yang cukup sejuk dan nyaman buat nongkrong. review_text: Its cozy coffeeshop and friendly staffs and owner. I actually become a regular out of necessities while waiting for my daughter finishing her english course. Despite that the staffs and owner are very friendly and nice. I did try their martabak sushi and french fries, actually those are quite good and I like it, the only problem is my concern on my high cholesterol level which prohibit me eating those regularly   but I do recommend those two foods.

This is the first time when ordering an Americano you can choose which coffee beans you can use, as far as I know, if you want to change beans you have to calibrate the espresso machine first, as a result the coffee I ordered tasted unpleasantly bitter. The coffee beans available have been in stock for so long that the coffee beans are very oily.

review_text: Near Jatinegara station There are 2 floors Excellent

I think the place is okay, especially for wfc/doing assignments because the table and chairs are also spacious, there are sockets too. The toilets are also clean and spacious. But unfortunately there is no prayer room. Then, if there are quite a lot of people, its a bit noisy because it seems like people dont come here to work, but to hang out with friends. Make food taste okay. The ice cream here is also delicious. Yesterday I tried the fried rice, it was also delicious, but the default seems to be spicy, so you have to say if you want it, its not spicy. The price here is probably not too expensive by Jakarta standards, but in my opinion its quite good because the fried rice is around 30k, the ice cream is also an average of around 20k, the drinks too. Sir, the one who served me was a bit less friendly yesterday, maybe he was just tired hahaha. Parking: Parking is on the side of the front road in the center of Batu Agate near the sidewalk and only motorbikes can do it, if you have a car its a bit difficult because the road is small. There is a parking attendant.

Tapi sayangnya gaada musholla. Terus kalo lumayan banyak orang agak berisik soalnya kayaknya orang ke sini bukan buat kerja gitu tapi buat ngumpul sama temen. Buat makanan rasanya oke. Es krimnya di sini juga enakk. Kemarin coba nasi gorengnya juga enak cuma kayaknya default pedes jadi harus ngomong kalo mau ga pedes. Harganya di sini mungkin untuk standar jakarta ga terlalu mahal, tpi menurutku aga lumayan si soalnya nasi gorengnya 30k es krimnya juga rata rata 20k-an, minumannya juga. Mas mas yang ngelayanin aku tpi kemaren aga kurang ramah mungkin dia lagi cape wkwkwk. Parking: Parkirnya di pinggir jalan depan yang pusat batu akik deket trotoar dan hanya bisa motor, kalo mobil agak sulit soalnya jalanannya kecil. Ada tukang parkir.

review_text: This is the first time I have come across a FULL BAMBOO coffee shop building design in the South Jakarta area! The location is very easy to access from anywhere, near Bintaro, Depok, Bekasi, etc. You could say this is a hidden gem, because the entrance is a bit deep into the housing complex. Suddenly I found a lush place with coconut trees and bamboo buildings. Favorite drink menu: BLACK CONAN! Must try! The combination of coffee, lemon and sweetness is perfect for afternoon until evening. Favorite food: KMJ CHICKEN NOODLES! The noodles are delicious, the chicken and mushrooms are really generous. Sweet and savory just right, the portion is also generous. Will come here often, because this environmentally friendly outdoor place is really cool :)
response_from_owner_text: Wow... Thank you very much, sis
review_translated_text: Baru pertama kali nemu desain bangunan coffee shop FULL BAMBU di daerah Jaksel! Lokasinya gampang banget diakses dari mana aja, dr Bintaro deket, dr Depok, Bekasi dll. Bisa dibilang ini hidden gem sih, karena masuknya agak ke dalem perumahan gitu. Tiba2 nemu tempat rimbun ada pohon kelapa sama bangunan bambu2 gitu. Menu favorit minuman: BLACK CONAN! Mesti dicoba! Perpaduan kopi, lemon sama manisnya pas banget buat sore sampe malem. Makanan favorit: MIE AYAM KMJ! Bakminya gurih, ayam sm jamurnya royal banget. Manis gurih pas, porsinya juga padet. Bakalan sering ke sini, karena tempat outdoor ramah lingkungan ini pewe banget :)

review_text: There are even more fun coffee spots in Cipinang Muara. MATA CAFE, located on Jalan Cipinang Muara 2, neighboring Malabar. Open from 3pm to 11pm... review_text: This restaurant is located in the PGC area, next to KFC. A restaurant that offers a variety of food at prices that I think are affordable. When I visited this restaurant, I tried one of the dishes on the menu, namely Soto Betawi + Rice (IDR 20,000,-) and for drinks I chose Melon Juice (IDR 10,000,-). In terms of taste, I think its delicious, the soto Betawi sauce is not too salty, the coconut milk is quite delicious, there are quite a lot of pieces of meat. And for the Melon Juice, its fresh and just the right amount of sweetness, great!
review_translated_text: Restoran ini lokasinya ada di dalam area PGC, sebelahan sama KFC. Restoran yang menawarkan berbagai macam makanan dengan harga yang menurut saya terjangkau. Pada saat saya berkunjung ke restoran ini, saya mencoba salah 1 makanan yang ada di daftar menu yaitu Soto Betawi + Nasi (IDR. 20.000,-) dan untuk minuman saya pilih Jus Melon (IDR. 10.000,-). Untuk rasanya menurut saya enak, kuah soto betawinya tidak terlalu asin, santannya cukup terasa, potongan dagingnya juga cukup banyak. Dan untuk Jus Melonnya, segar dan manisnya pas, mantab!

review_text: Syahnas Garden provides a variety of dishes that are appetizing, I finally ordered Soto Betawi with rice (Rp. 18,000), Kwetiauw (Rp. 17,000), soursop juice (Rp. 10,000) and Fresh Ice Tea (Rp. 3,000). Its not cheap to eat in a shopping center. The food is delicious, the prices are affordable, the place is neat and clean, which is my choice.
